The paper describes a technique for non-blocking implementations of tree data structures, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of LLX, SCX, and VLX primitives also suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the experimental performance analysis indicates a focus on efficiency and optimization, which could fall under the category of emerging technologies (cs.ET).
